- *Low-Dose Lithium — SPM Pro-Resolving Mediator Enhancement* ([Chapter 17 universal mechanisms, new paragraph in Family 19 (SPM deficiency) evidence status section; hypothesis registry, 1 new open-question entry O 0.15; references.bib, 11 new entries with `research_stream=lithium-spm-proresolving`; Appendix H, new annotated bib subsection]. The key finding: Basselin 2010 demonstrated chronic lithium increases brain 17-HDHA (the committed D-series resolvin/protectin precursor) 1.9-fold in rats — the only study directly linking lithium to SPM biosynthesis. Toricelli 2021's microdose lithium cytokine shift (IL-10↑, IL-6↓, IL-1α↓) is consistent with resolvin activity but SPMs were not measured. The complete chain (Li⁺→15-LOX→17-HDHA→RvD→GPCR→M2 shift) is assembled from separate literatures; no study has measured SPMs after lithium at any dose. The Basselin precursor increase and Toricelli cytokine shift make this a testable hypothesis, not an established mechanism. _Motivated by:_ Basselin 2010 @Basselin2010LithiumAA_DHA — chronic lithium increases brain 17-HDHA 1.9-fold (committed resolvin/protectin precursor); Toricelli 2021 @Toricelli2021MicrodoseLithiumInflammation — microdose lithium cytokine shift (IL-10↑/IL-6↓/IL-1α↓) consistent with resolvin activity.

