- *Land-based rowing (WaterRower) integration* ([Chapter 17, new section `subsec:land-rowing` with speculation `@spec:land-rowing` (cert 0.45) + new section `subsec:rowing-stroke-rate-dial` with speculation `@spec:rowing-stroke-rate-dial` (cert 0.50); Chapter 14, 1 reinforcement edit adding Dallas/Leeds POTS protocol citations `@Fu2010DallasProtocol @Fu2018ExercisePOTS` to graded reconditioning recommendation; Chapter 17, 1 reinforcement edit expanding Leeds protocol reference in constant-body-position section with protocol outcomes + cross-ref to new land-rowing section; modality classification Tier 2 updated to add land rowing; hypothesis registry, 2 new entries; references.bib, 3 new entries (Fu2010DallasProtocol cert 0.80, Fu2018ExercisePOTS cert 0.85, Kleshnev2004 cert 0.50); Appendix H, 4 new annotated entries]): Integrated land-based water-resistance rowing as a distinct Tier 2 modality from water-immersed rowing. Land rowing retains seated constant position and compound movement distribution but loses hydrostatic pressure benefit; it gains home accessibility — eliminating the pool transport barrier that consumes energy envelope. Dallas/Leeds POTS protocol (Fu et al. 2010, 2018) explicitly uses seated rowing as a starting modality alongside recumbent cycling and swimming, with 76 percent research completion, +8 percent peak VO2, +12 percent cardiac size, and +7 percent blood volume — dropping to 41 percent in community settings. Stroke-rate-as-dial speculation formalizes the precision titration strategy: operating at threshold −1 stroke/min as the calibrated maintenance rate within the therapeutic window. _Motivated by:_ @Fu2010DallasProtocol @Fu2018ExercisePOTS — Dallas/Leeds POTS protocol explicitly validating seated rowing as the lowest-orthostatic-demand Tier 2 modality, providing the strongest clinical precedent for land-based rowing in POTS+ME/CFS despite zero ME/CFS-specific rowing trial data.

